        <p>
          It was the first time we'd actually seen the place we were staying in. We learned
          a lot the first night. It was dark, there wasn't much privacy, and it would be an
          adventure.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the light of day, the place was a lot less scary. It was gorgeous. The light came
          bursting through the windows that were on nearly every wall and bounced cheerfully
          off the white beams of the ceiling.
        </p>
        <p>
          But my favorite part might be the way we could lay in bed and stare at the
          stars through the skylight in the ceiling. The sections of glass floor in the
          kitchen were a lot of fun and were just another way of making this house feel like
          a super cool treehouse.
