        <h2>Queen of the Coast</h2>
        <p>
        Our first beach trip was to the famous surf spot,
        <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Rincon+Beach+Park/@34.378217,-119.482154,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80e90894f5212d19:0x81822da9b27e2e77">Rincon Beach</a>.
          It was about a 45 minute drive from the house. We woke up early, explored the house,
          and had an amazing breakfast at Bonnie Lu's in downtown Ojai.
        </p>
        <p>
          The beach was so beautiful and so quiet. I think everyone had a very happy dog running
          around except for us. The waves were huge and there was a big group of surfers catching
          some pretty great ones.
        </p>
        <p>
          There were these blue and clear creatures all over the shore that I first thought
          were stingy jellyfish, but turned out to be harmless. They were really pretty and
          looked like glass. Rick got in some boogie boarding time while I soaked up the sun.
        </p>
        <p>When we got back to Ojai, we went to Boccali's for some delicious pizza.</p>
