        <h2>Santa Barbara Vineyards</h2>
        <p>
          We planned to spend my birthday visiting a couple of vineyards in Santa Barbara.
          We woke up early and had breakfast at Farmer and The Cook, which was actually an
          organic farm with a restaurant attached.
        </p>
        <p>
          We started driving up to Santa Barbara where the two vineyards were that we
          wanted to visit. The drive was so pretty. Such narrow winding roads through
          the mountains.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first vineyard on our list was <a href="http://www.rusack.com/">Rusack</a>. The
          place was really busy and we almost couldn't find a place to park. When we sat
          down outside under the trees, we instantly relaxed and took in the scenery of the
          vineyard and the rows and rows of grape vines. We brought cheese, crackers, and
          salami to snack on while we tasted 6 or 7 different wines.
        </p>
      </div>
